e just like any doctor would he said and then they were back on the shore where it all began the ufo was gone and parker said they tried to collect themselves hickson needed three shots of liquor from bottle in his car to calm his nerves before deciding to report what happened at the jackson county sheriff department deputies initially suspected both men were drunk glenn ryder who still works for the sheriff office said he laughed at the report but met with the men parker and hickson stuck to their story after the formal interview deputies left hickson and parker together in room with hidden tape recorder hoping to catch them in lie me and the other investigator got up and left to let them talk to see if they were going to say we got them fooled but they did ryder said they were really concerned on the tape hickson tells parker it scared me to death too son you ca get over it in lifetime jesus christ have mercy do know what happened to them ryder said was there with them but know you do fake fear and they were fearful they were fearful the next afternoon the story was splashed across the front pages of newspapers in pascagoula and gulfport overnight pascagoula became magnet for news reporters and ufo investigators widespread interest in ufos began in the 1940s with an incident at roswell in which ufo enthusiasts believe the government got its hands on crashed ufo and alien bodies the government spent decades denying it in the 1960s interest flared anew with series of reports including the purported alien abduction of new hampshire couple betty and barney hill in the widespread attention to the pascagoula encounter set off new round of reports in south mississippi hundreds of reports overwhelmed authorities in the two weeks after the encounter there were hoaxes and humor too long beach taxi driver told police being with pincers tapped on his window story he admitted days later was fake mobile television station said it would record ufo appearance predicted by psychic